review_blob: Not an easy drinking beer. Cloyingly sweet and very hoppy. Lots of flavor but couldnt even finish one.
Subtle citrus aroma with big IPA flavor. Nice creamy palate and good hop to malt balance.
Very creamy palate and full of complex flavors but for how famed it is I must say i was a bit dissapointed. The alcohol dominates the taste a bit more than i would like. Overall a great complex beer.
Very nice mango aroma. Great hop/malt balance. Not overly bitter and very drinkable for an imperial IPA. The alcohol is very well concealed.
Nice citrus aroma, a bit light on taste. Light bodied, refreshing. Could use more malt balance.
beer_name: BridgePort Trilogy 1 Crystal Dry-Hopped Pale Ale

review_blob: Definitely a mouthful. Tons of citrus hop flavor but well balanced by lots of malt sweetness. Cloudy appearance. Very good beer overall.
Interesting for a pumpkin, not what you expect upfront as the pumpkin spice is sort of a side note.  The beer is spritzy and very refreshing.  Very drinkable.
Scoth Ales are usually not my favorite but this one was well balanced, not overly sweet or alcoholic and with a very good creamy mouthfeel.  Good beer in a can!
Curvy bottle is different and somewhat cool, beer is very light with slight hint of hops and watery, corn flavor.  Another light commercial beer.
Not even worth rating, disgusting says it all. White foamy head, and watery taste.
A good, drinkable, fizzy porter.  Light roasted flavors with a good amount of carbonation and a dry finish.

At bottleworks on tap in a brandy snifter.  Creamy mouthfeel, slight hops flavor but enough to balance out the malt.  Alcohol taste definitely present but not overwhelming.  A cross between a pilsener and a brandy.  High gravity beers tend to not be my favorites, but this is a very good sipping beer.
On cask at the tap room.  Strong coffee flavor well balanced with malt and oats.  Medium bodied and very drinkable.
Very drinkable pale ale, with nice balance of malt and hops.  Slightly bitter with nice creamy mouthfeel and nice amber color.  A very good basic beer.
Pours very light straw yellow with soapy head that dissipates to nothing.  Slight aroma of hops but nothing more than another light industrial lager.
Very sweet, extra fizzy beer made to be a champagne alternative.  Interesting but not sure I could drink this for more than a taste.
Actually the better (cant say best for any of ILCs products) beer La Constancia makes, yet they market it as the cheapest, go figure.  Some hop flavor and aroma that helps disguise the corn.
So they change the name and make it even more watery, I wonder if they added more corn?
Flavors of corn with a slight hint of hops and malt.  Fake foamy white head.
Watery, with soapy looking white foam and taste of corn.  Another crap industrial.
Great IPA.  Pours dark golden color and aroma is amazing.  Floral, citrus.  Sweet malt taste perfectly balanced by substantial hoppy bitterness and spicyness.
Thick creamy black pour.  Extremely complex with tons of chocolate and coffee flavor and aroma.  Alcohol level is well hidden by complexity of flavors.  Best stout Ive tried.
Pours a clear, bright copper color with a beige foamy, long lasting head.  Sweet, spicy raisin flavors and good mouthfeel.
Pours light crystal clear copper color. Strong floral aroma. Sweet taste well balances by tons of  sticky hops.  Medium  body and citrus aftertaste. Another very good Lagunitas brew.

Pours clear light amber with some visible sediment suspended.  Shocking at first but it kind of grows on you.  Malty sweet smell and sweet spicy belgian taste, long lasting.  I find the alcohol content to make it a bit harsh but overall a good beer.
Pours golden and very clear.  Floral aroma and hoppy taste.  Very good winter ale.
On tap at the Country Club Bar and Grill in Chesterfield.  Pours a hazy amber.  Good malt/hop balance.  Floral and citrus flavors.  Good beer overall.
Malt with mild hop flavors and a rye finish.  Flavors dont blend all that well but it is drinkable.
Opaque copper color with small white head.  Malty sweet with medium hop bitterness.  Malty aroma.
A bit bitter, chocolatey, coffee flavors.  Not my favorite stout but ok to accompany lunch at Whole Foods.

Pours a very clear dark amber, spicy but not overly so.  Definite smell and taste of clove and citrus. A bit too alcoholic for my taste, could maybe use some more hop bitterness to balance it out.  Overall a good Christmas Ale.

Pours a nice copper color with hefty beige foam.  A very well balanced beer, especially considering it has 10% ABV.  If I hadnt read the label I never would have put the ABV this high.  Very floral and citrusy aroma and flavor combined with nutty smoked malt flavors in a perfect balance.   Overall a great brew.
Shared a couple of pints on tap with Dan Kopman at Bottleworks.  I really enjoyed this beer.  Hazy, amber in color with nice head.  Variety of fruit flavors.  Medium body. Well balanced flavor.
Bottle - pours hazy amber with small foamy white head.  Sweet candy flavors, light to medium palate.  Not bad for the price but nothing special.

Enjoyed 4 pints of these one afternoon at the Pub while watching Mark brew.  Very drinkable well balanced taste.  Nice reddish brown color and malty aroma.  Hints of fruit and light to medium body.  Very good beer overall.
Great IPA.  Normally not a big fan of IPAs but this beer was very flavorful but not overly bitter.  Has a somewhat sweet taste and floral aroma.

The best beer that can be found in El Salvador.  Much better than I expected a commercial stout to be and much better than any other guinness product.  Strong stout flavor and noticeable alcohol.  Smooth, full bodied beer.
While it did sort of look like  a Guinness it didnt taste much like one.  Tasted more like your regular big brewer lager, not bad on a hot sunny day.
A strong stout full of flavor and very noticeable alcohol. Youd better like dark beers before having this one.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Another good beer from Boulevard. Not overly complex flavors but definitely a solid porter.

Not a big fan of pumpkins and didnt think I would like a pumpkin ale but either this beer is well done or just the fact that it is beer made me like it.  Nice gentle taste of pumpkin and good tasting overall.
A great beer from Schlafly.  Solid stout flavor with a clear hint of wood.  While the alcohol can be tasted it doesnt overpower the flavor.
beer_name: Schlafly Reserve Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: We drank a 1 year old bottle and it had aged very well. Complex fruity flavors with earthy undertones.  A good amount of carbonation.  Overall a great saison with distinct brett funkiness.
Not a bad ale to enjoy with friends but also nothing that special about it.  The clove finish is interesting but overall it is a bit on the light side.

While I am somewhat knew at beer tasting, so far this is my favorite beer.  Stouts and Porters are my favorite types though.  Full bodied porter with smoky flavor and somewhat dry with a nice but not overwhelming bitterness to it.  Very nice dark color.  A great beer overall and now I cant wait to taste the Founders Breakfast Stout this weekend and find out what all the raving is about.
